The paper deals with implementing and comparing different dimensionality reduction techniques and classification algorithms on various datasets. This falls under the broad category of machine learning, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. The use of Deep Autoencoder and NCA techniques suggests a focus on deep learning and neural networks, which is covered by cs.LG. The application of these techniques on image and signal datasets (such as Movement Libras and Parkinsons) suggests a possible fit with cs.CV and cs.NE. The use of classification algorithms such as KNN, ENN, and SVM suggests a focus on supervised learning, which is covered by cs.AI and cs.DS. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, and cs.DS.
